-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party notice — NetHack / NLE / MiniHack
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Nethax is a from-scratch reimplementation of NetHack 3.7 and the NetHack
Learning Environment (NLE), built against canonical sources cloned into a
gitignored `vendor/` directory.  The MIT license above covers the JAX source,
tests, documentation, generated tile atlas, and accompanying assets in this
repository.

A small number of data tables and verbatim level-MAP strings are ported
bit-for-bit from NetHack 3.7 for parity testing.  NetHack itself is
distributed under the NetHack General Public License (NGPL), available at:

    https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/master/dat/license

Downstream redistribution of nethax that includes these vendor-derived
fragments may need to comply with NGPL terms.  See `docs/vendor_parity.md`
for a per-subsystem breakdown of what is reimplemented from scratch versus
what is verbatim, and which vendor file each citation points to.

The NLE benchmark surface (Gym/Gymnasium API, observation dict schema,
121-action enum, 5976-entry glyph2tile mapping) is reproduced for drop-in
compatibility; NLE itself is BSD-licensed.  See:

    https://github.com/facebookresearch/nle

MiniHack is similarly Apache-2.0 licensed; the curriculum-style envs under
`Nethax/minihax/` reimplement that interface from scratch.  See:

    https://github.com/facebookresearch/minihack
